text: Setúbal (, also , ) is a city and a municipality in Portugal. The population in 2021 was 123,496. In Setubal is Portugal’s largest covered market, and the Igreja do Convento de Jesus church. On the hill to the south of the city is the Forte de São Filipe, a fort constructed during the 16th century by the Spanish king, Philip II. ==References== Category:Cities in Portugal Category:Municipalities of Portugal
title: Setúbal
